#compdef kubediff
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# kubediff — "Source VS Deployed": Kubernetes manifest diff tool that
#            compares the YAML manifests on disk (after kustomize build
#            / helm template / plain `kubectl apply -f`) against the
#            live state of the corresponding resources in the cluster,
#            and produces a colorized Myers-diff highlighting the
#            drift.  The use case: "I have a GitOps repo with manifests
#            — what's actually deployed vs what the repo says should
#            be deployed?" (Rust, 184★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/Ramilito/kubediff
# author : Ramilito (Robin Wallin)
# license: MIT
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from
# src/main.rs on the Ramilito/kubediff tip — clap `#[derive(Parser)]`
# Cli struct + `#[derive(ValueEnum)]` CliLogLevel enum parsed exactly
# as declared.  The CLI is intentionally flat (no subcommands) — each
# invocation is a single drift-check pass against the configured
# paths.  Persistent configuration lives in `~/.config/kubediff/
# config.toml` (a `Settings::load()` call near the top of main()) so
# the CLI flag surface stays small.
#
# Direct deps from Cargo.toml (selected):
#   similar                "2.6"    ← canonical Rust text-diff library
#                                      (this axis) — by Armin Ronacher
#                                      (mitsuhiko/similar); pure-Rust
#                                      implementation of the Myers
#                                      diff algorithm + Patience diff
#                                      + LCS diff + line-level and
#                                      char-level granularity + an
#                                      ergonomic builder API for
#                                      formatting differences as
#                                      unified diff / inline diff /
#                                      side-by-side / colorized
#                                      terminal output.  Successor to
#                                      Ronacher's own `difflib` Python
#                                      port; the design intent is
#                                      "Python's difflib but with
#                                      Rust's type system + speed."
#                                      Supports `TextDiff::from_lines`
#                                      / `from_words` / `from_chars`
#                                      / `from_graphemes` for varying
#                                      granularity, and the
#                                      `algorithm::Algorithm` enum
#                                      selects between Myers /
#                                      Patience / LCS depending on
#                                      which tradeoff (speed vs
#                                      diff-quality) the consumer
#                                      needs.  THE Rust answer to
#                                      "compute and format the diff
#                                      between two strings" — used by
#                                      every Rust tool that displays
#                                      structured diffs: astral-sh/
#                                      ruff (Python linter — uses
#                                      similar for autofix preview),
#                                      biomejs/gritql (Biome's
#                                      structural search), sachaos/
#                                      viddy (modern `watch`), denoland
#                                      /deno_doc, LukeMathWalker/pavex
#                                      (Rust web framework — generates
#                                      diffs of generated code),
#                                      oppiliappan/statix (Nix linter),
#                                      Shemnei/punktf (dotfile
#                                      manager — diff between source
#                                      template and rendered config),
#                                      chaqchase/lla (modern `ls`
#                                      with snapshot-comparison
#                                      modes).  kubediff uses similar
#                                      inside src/lib.rs's Process
#                                      module — once the Kubernetes
#                                      live-state YAML is fetched
#                                      from the cluster via kube-rs
#                                      and the on-disk manifest is
#                                      loaded, both are serialized
#                                      to canonical YAML and fed to
#                                      `TextDiff::from_lines` to
#                                      produce the resource-level
#                                      diff that the CLI then
#                                      colorizes via the `colored`
#                                      crate and pretty-prints via
#                                      `bat` (the syntax-highlighted
#                                      cat replacement) when stdout
#                                      is a TTY.
#   kube                   "3.0.0"   (Kubernetes API client — kube-rs;
#                                      fetches the live state)
#   k8s-openapi            "0.27"    (typed Kubernetes resource
#                                      definitions matching the cluster
#                                      API surface)
#   tokio                            (async runtime for the kube-rs
#                                      client)
#   serde + serde_yaml + serde_json  (YAML/JSON parsing of both the
#                                      on-disk manifests and the
#                                      cluster responses)
#   bat                    "0.24.0"  (syntax-highlighted output when
#                                      a TTY is connected; falls back
#                                      to plain text when piped)
#   clap (with derive)               (CLI parser)
#   colored                          (terminal color codes for the
#                                      diff +/- line markers)
#   anyhow + dirs + glob             (error handling + config-dir
#                                      resolution + path globbing)
#
# kubediff fills a gap that vanilla `kubectl diff` doesn't quite cover:
# `kubectl diff -f manifest.yaml` does server-side dry-run apply +
# diff, but only against ONE manifest at a time and only for resources
# the manifest explicitly references.  kubediff scans a configured
# directory tree (typically a GitOps repo / Kustomize overlay /
# umbrella Helm chart output), enumerates every resource the manifests
# would create, fetches the actual live state from the cluster for
# each, and emits a unified diff of the field-by-field drift.  The
# `--env <env>` flag selects which kustomize overlay / Helm values set
# to apply before comparing (so `kubediff --env prod` and
# `kubediff --env staging` give the right diff for each environment
# without separate commands), and `--inplace` lets you operate on a
# pre-rendered manifest dir instead of running the build pipeline
# again.
#
# ============================================================================
# === AXIS 191 OPENS — text diff algorithm libraries =======================
# === Rust=246 OPENS at slot 1/0/0 ========================================
# ============================================================================
# Axis position: Rust=246 OPENS Axis 191 at slot 1/0/0 — the first of the
# three lanes for the canonical text diff algorithm library trio.  The
# axis anchors on a single pure-host-language implementation of Myers
# diff (or Patience diff, or LCS diff) with an API that returns
# structured diff operations (Insert / Delete / Replace / Equal) so
# downstream consumers can render them however they want — terminal
# unified diff, side-by-side, inline-word-highlight, HTML, JSON,
# whatever:
#
#     Rust    : similar                     by Armin Ronacher
#                                              (mitsuhiko/similar);
#                                              pure-Rust Myers +
#                                              Patience + LCS with
#                                              builder API for
#                                              unified / inline /
#                                              colorized formatting.
#                                              Successor to Ronacher's
#                                              own difflib Python port.
#                 → kubediff (Robin Wallin Ramilito — Kubernetes
#                              "Source VS Deployed" manifest diff
#                              tool; compares on-disk manifests
#                              against live cluster state via kube-rs;
#                              similar produces the line-level diff
#                              that bat syntax-highlights for the TTY
#                              output; 184★ MIT)
#                 _kubediff        [Rust=246 OPENS Axis 191, 1/0/0]
#                                                  ↑↑↑ THIS FILE ↑↑↑
#
#     Go      : (next round — Go=246, slot 2/0/0)
#                Canonical Go text-diff library: github.com/sergi/go-diff
#                by Sergio Acosta — Go port of Google's diff-match-
#                patch JavaScript library by Neil Fraser (the same
#                Myers-based diff algorithm with the additional
#                "patch" application surface that allows applying
#                diffs as transformations).  Used by every Go tool
#                that diffs text: golangci-lint, gopls (the Go LSP),
#                kubernetes itself for the kubectl diff implementation,
#                and many more.  [TBD next-round consumer]
#
#     JS/Node : (Axis 191 CLOSES at TS-Node=246, slot 1/1/1)
#                Canonical JS text-diff library: `diff` by Kevin Decker
#                (kpdecker/jsdiff) — pure-JS Myers diff with char /
#                word / line / sentence / CSS / JSON granularity
#                selectors.  Used by Mocha (for test diff output),
#                Jest (for snapshot diffs), every JS code-review tool,
#                Prettier (for printing the diff between formatted
#                and unformatted output).  Alternative: `diff-match-
#                patch` (google/diff-match-patch) — the original
#                Google library that sergi/go-diff is a port of;
#                still actively used in Node despite the older API.
#                [TBD closer consumer]
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=246     ← THIS FILE          (axis 191 OPENS, slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=246       ← next round         (axis 191 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=246  ← round after        (axis 191 CLOSES at triple-246, 1/1/1)
# ============================================================================

_kubediff() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]' \
        '(-e --env)'{-e,--env}'=[environment selector (matches a top-level key in ~/.config/kubediff/config.toml — typically `prod` / `staging` / `dev` — which controls the kustomize overlay or Helm values file the manifests are rendered with before comparison)]:env:' \
        '(-i --inplace)'{-i,--inplace}'[operate on already-rendered manifests in --path without running the build pipeline (kustomize build / helm template) again — useful when the manifests are pre-rendered by CI]' \
        '(-p --path)'{-p,--path}'=[explicit path to a directory of YAML manifests or a single .yaml file (overrides the path baked into the config file for the selected --env)]:path:_files' \
        '(-l --log)'{-l,--log}'=[set log verbosity (defaults to error from the config file)]:level:(info warning error)' \
        '(-t --term-width)'{-t,--term-width}'=[explicit terminal width for the diff output (default: auto-detect via ioctl TIOCGWINSZ)]:cols:'
}

_kubediff "$@"
